function.name: assert
function.summary: Asserts a value is non-nil, otherwise shows dialog and outputs debug diagnostic information if you have a debugger attached to wow.exe.

function.name: getfenv
function.summary: Returns the table representing the stack frame of the given function or stack level.
function.parameter: A function or an integer representing the stack level.
function.returns: A table representing the stack frame.

function.name: next
function.summary: Returns the next key, value pair of the table, allowing you to walk over the table.

function.name: pcall
function.summary: Returns a boolean value indicating successful execution of func and the error message or func's results as additional values.
function.returns: If the call to the function (that was passed to pcall) succeeded, returns true. If an error occured, returns false.

function.name: setfenv
function.summary: Sets the table representing the stack frame of the given function or stack level.
function.parameter: A function or an integer representing the stack level.
A table representing the stack frame.

function.name: type
function.summary: Returns the type of a variable as a string, "number", "string", "table", "function" or "userdata".
function.returns: Returns the type of a variable.

function.name: unpack
function.summary: Returns the contents of its argument as separate values.
function.returns: The contents of the argument as separate values.
